maining) during `PostCommit` processing. These stale sessions stick around only because their `LastCheckpointID` is needed for amend trailer restoration.\\n\\n### What it does\\n\\n1. **New field** `FullyCondensed bool` on `session.State` — marks sessions that have been condensed with zero remaining files\\n2. **Sets the flag** in `postCommitProcessSession` when `handler.condensed && phase == ENDED && len(FilesTouched) == 0`\\n3. **Skips** flagged sessions in the `PostCommit` loop (avoids re-resolving shadow branches, running transitions, etc.)\\n4. **Clears the flag** in `ActionClearEndedAt` so reactivated sessions aren't incorrectly skipped\\n\\n### Looks good\\n\\n- **Placement of the flag-setting logic** is correct — it's after the carry-forward calculation, so `FilesTouched` is already updated.\\n- **Clearing on reactivation** is done in the right place (`ActionClearEndedAt`), which fires on both `ENDED → ACTIVE` (TurnStart) and `ENDED → IDLE` (SessionStart). This covers both reactivation paths.\\n- **`omitempty` on JSON** — existing state files without the field will deserialize as `false`, so no migration needed.\\n- Comments are clear and explain the \\\"why\\\" well.\\n\\n### Concerns\\n\\n1. **No tests.** There are no unit tests for either behavior:\\n   - That `FullyCondensed` gets set when the conditions are met\\n   - That `PostCommit` actually skips fully-condensed sessions\\n   - That `ActionClearEndedAt` clears `FullyCondensed`\\n   \\n   Given the phase state machine already has good test coverage, adding a test for the `ActionClearEndedAt` clearing would be straightforward. And a test in the hooks for the skip behavior would guard against regressions.\\n\\n2. **The skip check only looks at `FullyCondensed`, not `Phase == ENDED`.** If there's ever a bug where `FullyCondensed` is set but the phase isn't ENDED (shouldn't happen with current code, but defensively):\\n\\n   ```go\\n   if state.FullyCondensed {\\n       continue\\n   }\\n   ```\\n\\n   Could be tightened to:\\n   ```go\\n   if state.FullyCondensed && state.Phase == session.PhaseEnded {\\n       continue\\n   }\\n   ```\\n\\n   This is minor — the `ActionClearEndedAt` reset makes it unlikely to be wrong — but it would be a cheap safety net.\\n\\n3. **Edge case: condensation succeeds but `saveSessionState` fails.** If the state save at line 963 fails after `FullyCondensed = true` is set in memory, the flag won't persist. On the next commit, the session will be processed again and re-condensed (which should be idempotent). This seems fine — just noting it's a no-op retry rather than data loss.\\n\\n### Verdict\\n\\nThe logic is correct and well-placed. The main gap is **missing tests** — I'd recommend adding at least a unit test for the `ActionClearEndedAt` clearing behavior and a test verifying the PostCommit skip. The defensive phase check (concern #2) is optional but cheap.\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":632,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":35762,\"output_tokens\":865,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":632,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYcqyUSs47PdpKnJimqST\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"e6833c0d-ab18-473b-967c-650e0725ba54\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-01T18:37:34.510Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"e6833c0d-ab18-473b-967c-650e0725ba54\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"db57b693-b4f5-47da-9cc5-651e9169ac1d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"skip-fully-condensed-sessions\",\"slug\":\"cozy-napping-bachman\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code 