te.FullyCondensed = false\\n```\\n\\n**New field** (`session/state.go`):\\n```go\\nFullyCondensed bool `json:\\\"fully_condensed,omitempty\\\"`\\n```\\n\\nThe purpose of this feature: ENDED sessions with no remaining work persist only for `LastCheckpointID` (amend trailer restoration). Before this change, every `PostCommit` call would still resolve shadow branches, run content checks, and execute the state machine for these dead sessions. The flag lets PostCommit skip them entirely.\\n\\nCheck for:\\n1. Is the skip check in the right place (before expensive operations like shadow branch resolution)?\\n2. Could the `sessions` slice itself be filtered earlier to avoid iterating over fully-condensed sessions?\\n3. Any concerns about the flag being checked without holding a lock (concurrent sessions)?\\n4. Is the condition `handler.condensed && state.Phase == session.PhaseEnded && len(state.FilesTouched) == 0` evaluated efficiently?\\n5. Any hot-path concerns with adding a bool field to session state (serialization overhead)?\"}]},\"uuid\":\"9a13626e-591f-4fcd-9d4e-ca074e8dfabf\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-01T20:11:26.719Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"Review this diff for efficiency issues: unnecessary work, missed concurrency, hot-path bloat, TOCTOU patterns, memory issues, overly broad operations.\\n\\nThe changes are in a Go CLI project's git hook handlers. Here's the production code context:\\n\\n**The skip optimization** (`manual_commit_hooks.go`):\\n```go\\n// In PostCommit, iterating over all sessions:\\nfor _, state := range sessions {\\n    // Skip fully-condensed ended sessions — no work remains.\\n    if state.FullyCondensed && state.Phase == session.PhaseEnded {\\n        continue\\n    }\\n    s.postCommitProcessSession(ctx, repo, state, ...)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Setting the flag** (same file, in `postCommitProcessSession`):\\n```go\\n// After carry-forward computation:\\nif handler.condensed && state.Phase == session.PhaseEnded && len(state.FilesTouched) == 0 {\\n    state.FullyCondensed = true\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Clearing the flag** (`session/phase.go`):\\n```go\\ncase ActionClearEndedAt:\\n    state.EndedAt = nil\\n    state.FullyCondensed = false\\n```\\n\\n**New field** (`session/state.go`):\\n```go\\nFullyCondensed bool `json:\\\"fully_condensed,omitempty\\\"`\\n```\\n\\nThe purpose of this feature: ENDED sessions with no remaining work persist only for `LastCheckpointID` (amend trailer restoration). Before this change, every `PostCommit` call would still resolve shadow branches, run content checks, and execute the state machine for these dead sessions. The flag lets PostCommit skip them entirely.\\n\\nCheck for:\\n1. Is the skip check in the right place (before expensive operations like shadow branch resolution)?\\n2. Could the `sessions` slice itself be filtered earlier to avoid iterating over fully-condensed sessions?\\n3. Any concerns about the flag being checked without holding a lock (concurrent sessions)?\\n4. Is the condition `handler.condensed && state.Phase == session.PhaseEnded && len(state.FilesTouched) == 0` evaluated efficiently?\\n5. Any hot-path concerns with adding a bool field to session state (serialization overhead)?\",\"agentId\":\"a01cd1a052f66820c\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01HJNoqk1URu2wWHAzC59tam\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01QCFR9pgvxo8KHSPiXfzXDC\",\"uuid\":\"d3e2afdf-6de4-4232-974e-aba368153688\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-01T20:11:26.719Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"d3e2afdf-6de4-4232-974e-aba368153688\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"db57b693-b4f5-47da-9cc5-651e9169ac1d\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"skip-fully-condensed-sessions\",\"slug\":\"cozy-napping-bachman\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01TA3ndTfDxUFqA8kF3wSZnf\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→//go:generate go run gen_state_diagram.go\\n     2→\\n     3→package session\\n     4→\\n     5→import (\\n     6→\\t\\\"context\\\"\\n     7→\\t\\\"fmt\\\"\\n     8→\\t\\\"log/slog\\\"\\n     9→\\t\\\"strings\\\"\\n    10→\\t\\\"time\\\"\\n    11→\\n    12→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/logging\\\"\\n    13→)\\n    14→\\n    15→// Phase represents the lifecycle stage of a session.\\n    16→type Phase string\\n    17→\\n    18→const (\\n    19→\\tPhaseActive Phase = \\\"active\\\"\\n    20→\\tPhaseIdle   Phase = \\\"idle\\\"\\n    21→\\tPhaseEnded  Phase = \\\"ended\\\"\\n    22→)\\n    23→\\n    24→// allPhases is the canonical list of phases for enumeration (e.g., diagram generation).\\n    25→var allPhases = []Phase{PhaseIdle, PhaseActive, PhaseEnded}\\n    26→\\n    27→// PhaseFromString normalizes a phase string, treating empty or unknown values\\n    28→// as PhaseIdle for backward compatibility with pre-state-machine session files.\\n    29→func PhaseFromString(s string) Phase {\\n    30→\\tswitch Phase(s) {\\n    31→\\tcase PhaseActive, \\\"active_committed\\\":\\n    32→\\t\\t// \\\"active_committed\\\" was removed with the 1:1 checkpoint model.\\n    33→\\t\\t// It previously meant \\\"agent active + commit happened during turn\\\".\\n    34→\\t\\t// Normalize to ACTIVE so HandleTurnEnd can finalize any pending checkpoints.\\n    35→\\t\\treturn PhaseActive\\n    36→\\tcase PhaseIdle:\\n    37→\\t\\treturn PhaseIdle\\n    38→\\tcase PhaseEnded:\\n    39→\\t\\treturn PhaseEnded\\n    40→\\tdefault:\\n    41→\\t\\t// Backward compat: truly unknown phases normalize to idle.\\n    42→\\t\\treturn PhaseIdle\\n    43→\\t}\\n    44→}\\n    45→\\n    46→// IsActive reports whether the phase represents an active agent turn.\\n    47→func (p Phase) IsActive() bool {\\n    48→\\treturn p == PhaseActive\\n    49→}\\n    50→\\n    51→// Event represents something that happened to a session.\\n    52→type Event int\\n    53→\\n    54→const (\\n    55→\\tEventTurnStart    Event = iota // Agent begins working on a prompt\\n    56→\\tEventTurnEnd                   // Agent finishes its turn\\n    57→\\tEventGitCommit                 // A git commit was made (PostCommit hook)\\n    58→\\tEventSessionStart              // Session process started (SessionStart hook)\\n    59→\\tEventSessionStop               // Session process ended (SessionStop hook)\\n    60→\\tEventCompaction                // Agent compacted context mid-turn (PreCompress hook)\\n    61→)\\n    62→\\n    63→// allEvents is the canonical list of events for enumeration.\\n    64→var allEvents = []Event{EventTurnStart, EventTurnEnd, EventGitCommit, EventSessionStart, EventSessionStop, EventCompaction}\\n    65→\\n    66→// String returns a human-readable name for the event.\\n    67→func (e Event) String() string {\\n    68→\\tswitch e {\\n    69→\\tcase EventTurnStart:\\n    70→\\t\\treturn \\\"TurnStart\\\"\\n    71→\\tcase EventTurnEnd:\\n    72→\\t\\treturn \\\"TurnEnd\\\"\\n    73→\\tcase EventGitCommit:\\n    74→\\t\\treturn \\\"GitCommit\\\"\\n    75→\\tcase EventSessionStart:\\n    76→\\t\\treturn \\\"SessionStart\\\"\\n    77→\\tcase EventSessionStop:\\n    78→\\t\\treturn \\\"SessionStop\\\"\\n    79→\\tcase EventCompaction:\\n    80→\\t\\treturn \\\"Compaction\\\"\\n    81→\\tdefault:\\n    82→\\t\\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\\\"Event(%d)\\\", int(e))\\n    83→\\t}\\n    84→}\\n    85→\\n    86→// Action represents a side effect that should be performed after a transition.\\n    87→// The caller is responsible for executing these -- the state machine only declares them.\\n    88→type Action int\\n    89→\\n    90→const (\\n    91→\\tActionCondense               Action = iota // Condense session data to permanent storage\\n    92→\\tActionCondenseIfFilesTouched               // Condense only if FilesTouched is non-empty\\n    93→\\tActionDiscardIfNoFiles                     // Discard session if FilesTouched is empty\\n    94→\\tActionWarnStaleSession                     // Warn user about stale session(s)\\n    95→\\tActionClearEndedAt                         // Clear EndedAt timestamp (session re-entering)\\n    96→\\tActionUpdateLastInteraction                // Update LastInteractionTime\\n    97→)\\n    98→\\n    99→// String returns a human-readable name for the action.\\n   100→func (a Action) String() string {\\n   101→\\tswitch a {\\n   102→\\tcase ActionCondense:\\n   103→\\t\\treturn \\\"Condense\\\"\\n   104→\\tcase ActionCondenseIfFilesTouched:\\n   105→\\t\\treturn \\\"CondenseIfFilesTouched\\\"\\n   106→\\tcase ActionDiscardIfNoFiles:\\n   107→\\t\\treturn \\\"DiscardIfNoFiles\\\"\\n   108→\\tcase ActionWarnStaleSession:\\n   109→\\t\\treturn \\\"WarnStaleSession\\\"\\n   110→\\tcase ActionClearEndedAt:\\n   111→\\t\\treturn \\\"ClearEndedAt\\\"\\n   112→\\tcase ActionUpdateLastInteraction:\\n   113→\\t\\treturn \\\"UpdateLastInteraction\\\"\\n   114→\\tdefault:\\n   115→\\t\\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\\\"Action(%d)\\\", int(a))\\n   116→\\t}\\n   117→}\\n   118→\\n   119→// TransitionContext provides read-only context for transitions that need\\n   120→// to inspect session state without mutating it.\\n   121→type TransitionContext struct {\\n   122→\\tHasFilesTouched    bool // len(FilesTouched) > 0\\n   123→\\tIsRebaseInProgress bool // .git/rebase-merge/ or .git/rebase-apply/ exists\\n   124→}\\n   125→\\n   126→// TransitionResult holds the outcome of a state machine transition.\\n   127→type TransitionResult struct {\\n   128→\\tNewPhase Phase\\n   129→\\tActions  []Action\\n   130→}\\n   131→\\n   132→// Transition computes the next phase and required actions given the current\\n   133→// phase and an event. This is a pure function with no side effects.\\n   134→//\\n   135→// Empty or unknown phase values are normalized to PhaseIdle for backward\\n   136→// compatibility with session state files created before phase tracking.\\n   137→func Transition(current Phase, event Event, ctx TransitionContext) TransitionResult {\\n   138→\\t// Normalize empty/unknown phase to idle for backward compatibility.\\n   139→\\tcurrent = PhaseFromString(string(current))\\n   140→\\n   141→\\tswitch current {\\n   142→\\tcase PhaseIdle:\\n   143→\\t\\treturn transitionFromIdle(event, ctx)\\n   144→\\tcase PhaseActive:\\n   145→\\t\\treturn transitionFromActive(event, ctx)\\n   146→\\tcase PhaseEnded:\\n   147→\\t\\treturn transitionFromEnded(event, ctx)\\n   148→\\tdefault:\\n   149→\\t\\t// PhaseFromString guarantees we only get known phases, but the\\n   150→\\t\\t// exhaustive linter requires handling the default case.\\n   151→\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{NewPhase: PhaseIdle}\\n   152→\\t}\\n   153→}\\n   154→\\n   155→func transitionFromIdle(event Event, ctx TransitionContext) TransitionResult {\\n   156→\\tswitch event {\\n   157→\\tcase EventTurnStart:\\n   158→\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{\\n   159→\\t\\t\\tNewPhase: PhaseActive,\\n   160→\\t\\t\\tActions:  []Action{ActionUpdateLastInteraction},\\n   161→\\t\\t}\\n   162→\\tcase EventTurnEnd:\\n   163→\\t\\t// Turn end while idle is a no-op (no active turn to end).\\n   164→\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{NewPhase: PhaseIdle}\\n   165→\\tcase EventGitCommit:\\n   166→\\t\\tif ctx.IsRebaseInProgress {\\n   167→\\t\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{NewPhase: PhaseIdle}\\n   168→\\t\\t}\\n   169→\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{\\n   170→\\t\\t\\tNewPhase: PhaseIdle,\\n   171→\\t\\t\\tActions:  []Action{ActionCondense, ActionUpdateLastInteraction},\\n   172→\\t\\t}\\n   173→\\tcase EventSessionStart:\\n   174→\\t\\t// Already condensable, no-op.\\n   175→\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{NewPhase: PhaseIdle}\\n   176→\\tcase EventSessionStop:\\n   177→\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{\\n   178→\\t\\t\\tNewPhase: PhaseEnded,\\n   179→\\t\\t\\tActions:  []Action{ActionUpdateLastInteraction},\\n   180→\\t\\t}\\n   181→\\tcase EventCompaction:\\n   182→\\t\\t// Compaction while idle shouldn't happen, but condense if there's work.\\n   183→\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{\\n   184→\\t\\t\\tNewPhase: PhaseIdle,\\n   185→\\t\\t\\tActions:  []Action{ActionCondenseIfFilesTouched, ActionUpdateLastInteraction},\\n   186→\\t\\t}\\n   187→\\tdefault:\\n   188→\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{NewPhase: PhaseIdle}\\n   189→\\t}\\n   190→}\\n   191→\\n   192→func transitionFromActive(event Event, ctx TransitionContext) TransitionResult {\\n   193→\\tswitch event {\\n   194→\\tcase EventTurnStart:\\n   195→\\t\\t// Ctrl-C recovery: agent crashed or user interrupted mid-turn.\\n   196→\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{\\n   197→\\t\\t\\tNewPhase: PhaseActive,\\n   198→\\t\\t\\tActions:  []Action{ActionUpdateLastInteraction},\\n   199→\\t\\t}\\n   200→\\tcase EventTurnEnd:\\n   201→\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{\\n   202→\\t\\t\\tNewPhase: PhaseIdle,\\n   203→\\t\\t\\tActions:  []Action{ActionUpdateLastInteraction},\\n   204→\\t\\t}\\n   205→\\tcase EventGitCommit:\\n   206→\\t\\tif ctx.IsRebaseInProgress {\\n   207→\\t\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{NewPhase: PhaseActive}\\n   208→\\t\\t}\\n   209→\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{\\n   210→\\t\\t\\tNewPhase: PhaseActive,\\n   211→\\t\\t\\tActions:  []Action{ActionCondense, ActionUpdateLastInteraction},\\n   212→\\t\\t}\\n   213→\\tcase EventSessionStart:\\n   214→\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{\\n   215→\\t\\t\\tNewPhase: PhaseActive,\\n   216→\\t\\t\\tActions:  []Action{ActionWarnStaleSession},\\n   217→\\t\\t}\\n   218→\\tcase EventSessionStop:\\n   219→\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{\\n   220→\\t\\t\\tNewPhase: PhaseEnded,\\n   221→\\t\\t\\tActions:  []Action{ActionUpdateLastInteraction},\\n   222→\\t\\t}\\n   223→\\tcase EventCompaction:\\n   224→\\t\\t// Compaction mid-turn: save current progress but stay active.\\n   225→\\t\\t// The transcript offset will be reset by the compaction handler.\\n   226→\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{\\n   227→\\t\\t\\tNewPhase: PhaseActive,\\n   228→\\t\\t\\tActions:  []Action{ActionCondenseIfFilesTouched, ActionUpdateLastInteraction},\\n   229→\\t\\t}\\n   230→\\tdefault:\\n   231→\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{NewPhase: PhaseActive}\\n   232→\\t}\\n   233→}\\n   234→\\n   235→func transitionFromEnded(event Event, ctx TransitionContext) TransitionResult {\\n   236→\\tswitch event {\\n   237→\\tcase EventTurnStart:\\n   238→\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{\\n   239→\\t\\t\\tNewPhase: PhaseActive,\\n   240→\\t\\t\\tActions:  []Action{ActionClearEndedAt, ActionUpdateLastInteraction},\\n   241→\\t\\t}\\n   242→\\tcase EventTurnEnd:\\n   243→\\t\\t// Turn end while ended is a no-op.\\n   244→\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{NewPhase: PhaseEnded}\\n   245→\\tcase EventGitCommit:\\n   246→\\t\\tif ctx.IsRebaseInProgress {\\n   247→\\t\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{NewPhase: PhaseEnded}\\n   248→\\t\\t}\\n   249→\\t\\tif ctx.HasFilesTouched {\\n   250→\\t\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{\\n   251→\\t\\t\\t\\tNewPhase: PhaseEnded,\\n   252→\\t\\t\\t\\tActions:  []Action{ActionCondenseIfFilesTouched, ActionUpdateLastInteraction},\\n   253→\\t\\t\\t}\\n   254→\\t\\t}\\n   255→\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{\\n   256→\\t\\t\\tNewPhase: PhaseEnded,\\n   257→\\t\\t\\tActions:  []Action{ActionDiscardIfNoFiles, ActionUpdateLastInteraction},\\n   258→\\t\\t}\\n   259→\\tcase EventSessionStart:\\n   260→\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{\\n   261→\\t\\t\\tNewPhase: PhaseIdle,\\n   262→\\t\\t\\tActions:  []Action{ActionClearEndedAt},\\n   263→\\t\\t}\\n   264→\\tcase EventSessionStop:\\n   265→\\t\\t// Already ended, no-op.\\n   266→\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{NewPhase: PhaseEnded}\\n   267→\\tcase EventCompaction:\\n   268→\\t\\t// Compaction while ended shouldn't happen, no-op.\\n   269→\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{NewPhase: PhaseEnded}\\n   270→\\tdefault:\\n   271→\\t\\treturn TransitionResult{NewPhase: PhaseEnded}\\n   272→\\t}\\n   273→}\\n   274→\\n   275→// ActionHandler defines strategy-specific side effects for state transitions.\\n   276→// The compiler enforces that every strategy-specific action has a handler.\\n   277→type ActionHandler interface {\\n   278→\\tHandleCondense(state *State) error\\n   279→\\tHandleCondenseIfFilesTouched(state *State) error\\n   280→\\tHandleDiscardIfNoFiles(state *State) error\\n   281→\\tHandleWarnStaleSession(state *State) error\\n   282→}\\n   283→\\n   284→// NoOpActionHandler is a default ActionHandler where all methods are no-ops.\\n   285→// Embed this in handler structs to only override the methods you need.\\n   286→type NoOpActionHandler struct{}\\n   287→\\n   288→func (NoOpActionHandler) HandleCondense(_ *State) error               { return nil }\\n   289→func (NoOpActionHandler) HandleCondenseIfFilesTouched(_ *State) error { return nil }\\n   290→func (NoOpActionHandler) HandleDiscardIfNoFiles(_ *State) error       { return nil }\\n   291→func (NoOpActionHandler) HandleWarnStaleSession(_ *State) error       { return nil }\\n   292→\\n   293→// ApplyTransition applies a TransitionResult to state: sets the new phase\\n   294→// unconditionally, then executes all actions. Common actions\\n   295→// (UpdateLastInteraction, ClearEndedAt) always run regardless of handler\\n   296→// errors so that bookkeeping fields stay consistent with the new phase.\\n   297→// Strategy-specific handler actions stop on the first error; subsequent\\n   298→// handler actions are skipped but common actions continue. Returns the\\n   299→// first handler error, or nil.\\n   300→func ApplyTransition(ctx context.Context, state *State, result TransitionResult, handler ActionHandler) error {\\n   301→\\tlogCtx := logging.WithComponent(ctx, \\\"session\\\")\\n   302→\\n   303→\\tactionStrs := make([]string, len(result.Actions))\\n   304→\\tfor i, a := range result.Actions {\\n   305→\\t\\tactionStrs[i] = a.String()\\n   306→\\t}\\n   307→\\tlogging.Debug(logCtx, \\\"ApplyTransition\\\",\\n   308→\\t\\tslog.String(\\\"session_id\\\", state.SessionID),\\n   309→\\t\\tslog.String(\\\"old_phase\\\", string(state.Phase)),\\n   310→\\t\\tslog.String(\\\"new_phase\\\", string(result.NewPhase)),\\n   311→\\t\\tslog.String(\\\"actions\\\", strings.Join(actionStrs, \\\",\\\")),\\n   312→\\t)\\n   313→\\n   314→\\tstate.Phase = result.NewPhase\\n   315→\\n   316→\\tvar handlerErr error\\n   317→\\tfor _, action := range result.Actions {\\n   318→\\t\\tswitch action {\\n   319→\\t\\t// Common actions: always applied, even after a handler error.\\n   320→\\t\\tcase ActionUpdateLastInteraction:\\n   321→\\t\\t\\tnow := time.Now()\\n   322→\\t\\t\\tstate.LastInteractionTime = &now\\n   323→\\t\\tcase ActionClearEndedAt:\\n   324→\\t\\t\\tstate.EndedAt = nil\\n   325→\\t\\t\\tstate.FullyCondensed = false\\n   326→\\n   327→\\t\\t// Strategy-specific actions: skip remaining after the first handler error.\\n   328→\\t\\tcase ActionCondense:\\n   329→\\t\\t\\tif handlerErr == nil {\\n   330→\\t\\t\\t\\tif err := handler.HandleCondense(state); err != nil {\\n   331→\\t\\t\\t\\t\\thandlerErr = fmt.Errorf(\\\"%s: %w\\\", action, err)\\n   332→\\t\\t\\t\\t}\\n   333→\\t\\t\\t}\\n   334→\\t\\tcase ActionCondenseIfFilesTouched:\\n   335→\\t\\t\\tif handlerErr == nil {\\n   336→\\t\\t\\t\\tif err := handler.HandleCondenseIfFilesTouched(state); err != nil {\\n   337→\\t\\t\\t\\t\\thandlerErr = fmt.Errorf(\\\"%s: %w\\\", action, err)\\n   338→\\t\\t\\t\\t}\\n   339→\\t\\t\\t}\\n   340→\\t\\tcase ActionDiscardIfNoFiles:\\n   341→\\t\\t\\tif handlerErr == nil {\\n   342→\\t\\t\\t\\tif err := handler.HandleDiscardIfNoFiles(state); err != nil {\\n   343→\\t\\t\\t\\t\\thandlerErr = fmt.Errorf(\\\"%s: %w\\\", action, err)\\n   344→\\t\\t\\t\\t}\\n   345→\\t\\t\\t}\\n   346→\\t\\tcase ActionWarnStaleSession:\\n   347→\\t\\t\\tif handlerErr == nil {\\n   348→\\t\\t\\t\\tif err := handler.HandleWarnStaleSession(state); err != nil {\\n   349→\\t\\t\\t\\t\\thandlerErr = fmt.Errorf(\\\"%s: %w\\\", action, err)\\n   350→\\t\\t\\t\\t}\\n   351→\\t\\t\\t}\\n   352→\\t\\tdefault:\\n   353→\\t\\t\\tif handlerErr == nil {\\n   354→\\t\\t\\t\\thandlerErr = fmt.Errorf(\\\"un