learsFullyCondensed` are nearly identical. The only differences are:\\n\\n- The `NewPhase` (`PhaseActive` vs `PhaseIdle`)\\n- The `Actions` list (one includes `ActionUpdateLastInteraction`, the other does not)\\n- The assertion message string\\n\\nHowever, both are testing the **same behavior**: that `ActionClearEndedAt` clears `FullyCondensed`. The `NewPhase` and extra actions are incidental to what's being tested. These two cases could be folded into the existing `TestApplyTransition_ClearsEndedAt` test (line 503) by upgrading it to table-driven:\\n\\n```go\\nfunc TestApplyTransition_ClearsEndedAt(t *testing.T) {\\n    t.Parallel()\\n\\n    tests := []struct {\\n        name     string\\n        newPhase Phase\\n        actions  []Action\\n    }{\\n        {\\n            name:     \\\"SessionStart_to_IDLE\\\",\\n            newPhase: PhaseIdle,\\n            actions:  []Action{ActionClearEndedAt},\\n        },\\n        {\\n            name:     \\\"TurnStart_to_ACTIVE\\\",\\n            newPhase: PhaseActive,\\n            actions:  []Action{ActionClearEndedAt, ActionUpdateLastInteraction},\\n        },\\n    }\\n\\n    for _, tt := range tests {\\n        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\\n            t.Parallel()\\n            endedAt := time.Now().Add(-time.Hour)\\n            state := &State{Phase: PhaseEnded, EndedAt: &endedAt, FullyCondensed: true}\\n            handler := &mockActionHandler{}\\n            result := TransitionResult{NewPhase: tt.newPhase, Actions: tt.actions}\\n\\n            err := ApplyTransition(context.Background(), state, result, handler)\\n\\n            require.NoError(t, err)\\n            assert.Nil(t, state.EndedAt)\\n            assert.False(t, state.FullyCondensed,\\n                \\\"FullyCondensed must be cleared when ActionClearEndedAt runs\\\")\\n        })\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThis would also subsume the pre-existing `TestApplyTransition_ClearsEndedAt` test (which is the same thing minus the `FullyCondensed: true` 